{"stat": "ok", "comments": {"comment": [{"permalink": "http://www.flickr.com/photos/library_of_congress/9687287516/#comment72157635403900929", "realname": "", "path_alias": null, "author": "66311327@N05", "iconserver": "7333", "datecreate": "1378485955", "_content": "&quot;Pasquale Amato (21 March 1878 \u2013 12 August 1942) was an Italian operatic baritone. Amato enjoyed an international reputation but attained the peak of his fame in New York City, where he sang with the Metropolitan Opera from 1908 until 1921.&quot;\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pasquale_Amato\" rel=\"nofollow\">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pasquale_Amato</a>\n\nOther Bain photos of him:\n<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/library_of_congress/3102889666/\" title=\"Amato as \"><img src=\"http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3036/3102889666_50fc62795d_m.jpg\" width=\"174\" height=\"240\" alt=\"Amato as \" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/library_of_congress/2422671709/\" title=\"Scotti; Amato; Hinshaw  (LOC) by The Library of Congress, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2060/2422671709_13c702e3e0_m.jpg\" width=\"174\" height=\"240\" alt=\"Scotti; Amato; Hinshaw  (LOC)\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/library_of_congress/2948799197/\" title=\"Antonio Scotti, Lucrezia Bori, Pasquale Amato  (LOC) by The Library of Congress, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3210/2948799197_1104090603_m.jpg\" width=\"174\" height=\"240\" alt=\"Antonio Scotti, Lucrezia Bori, Pasquale Amato  (LOC)\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/library_of_congress/9470271985/\" title=\"P. Amato  (LOC) by The Library of Congress, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5532/9470271985_0f5355c64b_m.jpg\" width=\"167\" height=\"240\" alt=\"P. Amato  (LOC)\" /></a>", "authorname": "B-59", "id": "8602872-9687287516-72157635403900929", "iconfarm": 8}, {"permalink": "http://www.flickr.com/photos/library_of_congress/9687287516/#comment72157635411288234", "realname": "", "path_alias": null, "author": "66311327@N05", "iconserver": "7333", "datecreate": "1378486565", "_content": "Mario and Spartaco were his <del>brothers</del> sons (PS: thanks to [http://www.flickr.com/photos/artolog]), see <a href=\"http://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive-free/pdf?res=F60D16FD345F13738DDDA80A94DA415B838DF1D3\" rel=\"nofollow\">The New York Times, December 21, 1913</a>", "authorname": "B-59", "id": "8602872-9687287516-72157635411288234", "iconfarm": 8}, {"permalink": "http://www.flickr.com/photos/library_of_congress/9687287516/#comment72157635415985626", "realname": "Art Siegel", "path_alias": "artolog", "author": "76016463@N00", "iconserver": "3807", "datecreate": "1378514688", "_content": "Not his brothers, but his sons.  According to information in the Times article, the older son Spartaco was born about 1901.  He was married to Egeria Guerrera Amato. \n<a href=\"http://etd.lsu.edu/docs/available/etd-11112009-092220/unrestricted/Kaufman_thesis.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">etd.lsu.edu/docs/available/etd-11112009-092220/unrestrict...</a>\nMario, born about 1903, was still living in New York in 1943 when he had a scrape with the law.\n<a href=\"http://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F6071FFF395C167B93CAA81789D95F478485F9\" rel=\"nofollow\">select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F6071FFF395C167B...</a>", "authorname": "artolog", "id": "8602872-9687287516-72157635415985626", "iconfarm": 4}, {"permalink": "http://www.flickr.com/photos/library_of_congress/9687287516/#comment72157635661182716", "realname": "Kristi", "path_alias": "kristi_loc", "author": "34904489@N07", "iconserver": "3309", "datecreate": "1379619729", "_content": "B-59 and artolog: Thanks for exploring the life of the Amato family so that we can expand the descriptive information in this record.", "authorname": "Kristi (LOC P&P)", "id": "8602872-9687287516-72157635661182716", "iconfarm": 4}], "photo_id": "9687287516"}}